text=(:comment a few notes about the recipe are sometimes nice:)%0a[[#excerpt]]%0aGrilled cheese sammiches are the traditional midwestern comfort food. Paired with tomato soup, they are wonderful for when things are cold and blowy, or when you don't want to think about what to make.%0a[[#excerptend]]%0a%0a[[#ingredients]]%0a!!Ingredients%0a(:comment bulleted list of ingredients, with notes if necessary:)%0a* 2 slices of any kind of bread%0a* butter, for outsides of bread%0a* cheese. Lots, various kinds, whatever. It works best in slices.%0a%0a[[#additions]]%0a!!!Additions:%0a''So many things can be added to the basic grilled cheese, here are but a few:''%0a* sliced tomatoes%0a* bacon strips%0a* mashed avocado or guacamole%0a* cold cuts%0a* liverwurst%0a* pickles%0a''Spread on inside of bread:''%0a* peanut butter%0a* pesto%0a* flavoured mayo spreads%0a* mustard%0a%0a%0a%0a[[#directions]]%0a!!Directions%0a(:comment ordered list of steps to follow:)%0a%0a# warm up a pan or griddle. [^The heat of the griddle/pan will depend on how long you grill for -- don't set the heat too high as it is much more likely to end up with charred bread and solid insides. Lower heat is more easily managed.^]'^,^' [^If you have a sandwich/panini grill, or one of those George Foreman Grills, they can make doing grilled cheese really easy, grilling both sided of the sandwich at the same time, and smooshing it a bit to give some extra tooth.^]%0a%0a# butter the outsides of both slices of bread.%0a%0a# when the griddle/pan is hot, lay one slice of bread, butter-side down, on the griddle.%0a%0a# layer on the slices of cheese you want. Use a fairly good amount. Mixing varieties of cheese is also pretty wonderful.%0a%0a# layer on whatever [[#additions|additions]] you want.%0a%0a# place the top slice of bread, butter-side up, on top.%0a%0a# let grill for about 5 minutes on the side. Flip entire sandwich over and grill other side for about 5 minutes. %0a%0a(:comment         Other sections as desired, remove if false/ifend pairs  to use:)%0a%0a(:if false:)%0a[[#variations]]%0a!!Variations%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a%0a[[#comments]]%0a!!Comments%0a%0a[^#^]%0a%0a%0a(:if false:)%0aSummary:comfort food%0aParent:(Recipes.)Lunch%0aIncludeMe:[[Lunch]]%0aTags:grilled cheese, cheese, sandwiches%0a(:tags-hide grilled cheese, cheese, sandwiches:)%0aCategories:[[!Lunch]]%0aSource:%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a
